caption: Food was tasty, but they didn’t fill up the quart container for the Panang curry entree. It cost about $15 for this and came with a small container of rice.  Also had the basil pad Thai, that was yummy. They use roasted chili flakes, which gives it a smoky flavor.

Like most Thai/Chinese restaurants, there are LOTS of options here, so most will find something they'll enjoy. I'm partial to fried rice, and there's plenty of options there so I can vary my orders. All of the fried rice options are great, but I can't say the same for others dishes, as I haven't tried them.  Prices are decent, considering you get so much food. There is a $10 minimum for card purchases, so unless you have cash, you won't be spending any less than $10 here. It can very well be split into two meals, however.  The service is friendly and speedy. They don't seem to speak the greatest English, but that's completely fine provided you don't have some kind of strange request, or if you have some kind of particular allergy.  There seems to be lots of seating here, which is nice. It definitely gets full around lunchtime, though. All in all, nice place to grab some good Thai food; just wish the prices could come down a bit, or they could remove that card minimum.

I will start out by saying that the food they served was fine.  My negative experience was purely related to their service. I ordered a delivery order for 40 people which was to be delivered at 11:30 am for an important meeting.  I confirmed with them umpteen times and had even turned down ordering at other restaurants who told me they could only deliver at 11:45. Well....turns out Nud Pob Thai opens at 11:30 and they were able to get me my food at 12:15, 45 minutes late and halfway through my meeting.  Not only that, but they misinformed me over the phone and even hung up on me once when I was calling to ask where my food was.  It felt dishonest on their part and was a very negative experience for me.  Be careful in your dealings with this restaurant.

Delicious! I pretty much always get the same thing, tofu larb, but I am a tofu larb connoisseur and the fact that I keep going back to this restaurant indicates they know how to put out some really good, authentic food. I no longer live in Boston, so any time I get to eat here, it's kind of a big deal. Today is a lucky day because I'm going to pick up an order very soon!  In all seriousness though, they have a huge menu, the people at the counter are always pleasant, and the place always looks clean & tidy to me. It's a tad pricey, but it is so reliably appetizing that it's worth it. When school is in session, it's kind of a madhouse. Yet they still crank through the orders and put out yummy food very efficiently. Going in the summer is better, only because you barely have to wait.  Any season, I highly recommend this restaurant!
